channel.title: [194 look-alike] Osiris ~ Continued
channel.description:
[img]http://oi44.tinypic.com/258uop5.jpg[/img]
[b]Hello everyone[/b]. It was a while since I was doing anything that was based on RuneScape Private Servers, and I felt like starting again so here I am. I'm continuing my [b]194 look-alike[/b] project called [b]Osiris[/b], which I started a year ago(or 2, I don't even know) because I felt like doing something different. Unfortunately I'm not so good with clients and stuff, so that will be the biggest problem for me now. I have the [b]194 maps[/b] and everything, just don't know what to do with it and how.
[img]http://oi43.tinypic.com/220o78.jpg[/img] This project is so fun, so I'm having a good time while coding this project.. There's not alot of people that are going to work on projects like this, that's what makes 'em [b]special[/b] B)
Here's a picture of the old school login Welcome Screen:
[img]http://oi42.tinypic.com/whmfip.jpg[/img] Server features: [code] Running Bones burying Emote animations Working PVP system Fletching with Interfaces (needs improvement) SkillInterfaces (Only attack for now, have to finish all of 'em) Teleporting (gfx,emote needed and some work on the timers) There's a command system that should be really improved too. Leveling up with interfaces Smelting ItemOnItem ItemOnObject Perfect door system Bones on altar Filling via fountains (waterskins, vials, bowls..) Music system [/code]
So yeah I'll do my best to create something beautiful out of this, if I learn how to load the maps and everything it will be brilliant.
[b][i][u]Goals (for now) :[/u][/i][/b]
[ul][li]Crafting[/li] [li]Improve fletching[/li] [li]Herb cleaning[/li] [li]Using bones on altar[/li] [li]Improve the PVP system[/li] [li]Finish the skill menus[/li] [li]Messaging ( Friend/Ignore list and stuff)[/li] [li]Dialogues[/li] [li]Smelting[/li] [li]Load the original 194 maps on the look-alike client[/li] [li]ItemOnObject[/li] [li]Filling via fountains[/li] [li]Npc's spawn - Varrock, Falador, Lumbridge, Edgeville, Camelot[/li] [li]Teleporting with anims and gfx[/li] [li]Pottery[/li][/ul] The log is starting from now. [code] 12.9.2013 23:17 - Started with smelting - The interface opens by clicking on the object - Proper level requirments, item adding/removing, item requirments and other - Started working on all bars 13.9.2013 00:15 - Smelting is finished 14.9.2013 18:34 - Started with Crafting - interfaces, AB 16.9.2013 16:26 - ItemOnObject class - Starting with bones on altar - Finished bones on altar - Filling via fountains - bowls, waterskins, vials.. - Added music system 17.9.2013 20:15 - Started adding Npc's at Varrock - All Npc's at Varrock are added in the npc spawn, time to do something more sexy - Started with Pottery, loading interface getting the item id's, strings and stuff 3.10.2013 23:00 - Vials/jugs.. has their own class now, cleaning the server a bit - Fixed the smelting interface, added the right items on interface. looks sexy now
[/code] I will put here some other pictures of the server. (I'll keep them updated after few updates)
The emote animations : [img]http://oi42.tinypic.com/333fwcm.jpg[/img]
Npcs at Varrock :) [img]http://oi43.tinypic.com/2d82b9x.jpg[/img]
Here's a preview of the fletching menu, looks pretty sexy though
[img]http://oi42.tinypic.com/2iik3g0.jpg[/img]
[img]http://oi39.tinypic.com/wcn7r8.jpg[/img]
The attack interface:
[img]http://oi44.tinypic.com/2r4olsj.jpg[/img]
Smelting Fully Works, including:
[ul][li]Interface/AB[/li] [li]Lvl requirements[/li] [li]Item Requirments[/li] [li]Emote[/li] [li]Messaging[/li][/ul] [img]http://oi41.tinypic.com/5expgw.jpg[/img][img]http://oi39.tinypic.com/2qut445.jpg[/img] [img]http://oi44.tinypic.com/35c51dc.jpg[/img] Smelting with emotes :) [img]http://oi42.tinypic.com/294t274.jpg[/img]
Started with crafting, should be finished soon I guess :) Looks pretty sexy, doesn't it? :D [img]http://oi42.tinypic.com/2mh97nt.jpg[/img]
Leveling up [img]http://oi40.tinypic.com/2zq7z0m.jpg[/img]
I will keep the post updated after every better update, there will be an update log too.
Credits:
[ul][li]Blake[/li] [li]Dakota[/li] [li]Diego (me)[/li][/ul]
